Package: OpTop
Type: Package
Title: Optimal Topic Selection and Goodness-of-Fit for Topic Models
Version: 0.20.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Francesco", "Grossetti", email = "francesco.grossetti@unibocconi.it",
    role = c("cre", "aut", "cph"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5130-7745")),
    person("Craig", "Lewis", email = "craig.lewis@owen.vanderbilt.edu", role = c("aut", "cph"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8734-1702")),
    person("Mattia", "Tamellini", email = "mattia.tamellini@gmail.com", role = "ctb"))
Description: Statistical tests, goodness-of-fit indices, and held-out
    validation for topic models. Implements the parametric selection of the
    number of topics of Lewis and Grossetti (2022)
    <https://jmlr.org/papers/v23/19-297.html> with bootstrap and
    moment-matched calibration, harmonized discrepancy indices at the
    document and word level, held-out and V-fold cross-fitted evaluation
    with moment-based specification tests, and an engine-agnostic adapter
    layer covering 'topicmodels', 'seededlda', and 'text2vec' fits, with
    compiled kernels that scale to corpora of tens of millions of
    documents.
